In England, in the seven days to 21 January, there were 563,231 new confirmed cases (996.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 January, there were 559,464 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 1% (3,767 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 26 January is 13,732,435 (24,283.6 cases per 100,000 population).
